stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> IDLE

    IDLE --> RESERVING: reserve LSN range
    RESERVING --> RESERVED: LogRange assigned
    RESERVED --> WRITING_BUFFER: encode redo into buffer segment
    WRITING_BUFFER --> RECENT_WRITTEN_PENDING: buffer bytes published
    RECENT_WRITTEN_PENDING --> READY_FOR_WRITE: contiguous range closed

    READY_FOR_WRITE --> FILE_WRITING: log writer owns file write lock
    FILE_WRITING --> WRITTEN: writeLsn advanced
    WRITTEN --> FILE_FLUSHING: flush policy requires fsync
    FILE_FLUSHING --> FLUSHED: flushedLsn advanced

    RECENT_WRITTEN_PENDING --> RECENT_CLOSED_PENDING: MTR dirty publish done
    RECENT_CLOSED_PENDING --> WAITING_WRITTEN: caller waits for write
    RECENT_CLOSED_PENDING --> WAITING_FLUSHED: caller waits for fsync
    RECENT_CLOSED_PENDING --> RELEASED: no durability wait

    WAITING_WRITTEN --> RELEASED: writeLsn reaches target
    WAITING_FLUSHED --> RELEASED: flushedLsn reaches target

    IDLE --> WAITING_SPACE: checkpoint age too high
    WAITING_SPACE --> RESERVING: checkpoint advances

    FILE_WRITING --> ERROR_BROADCAST: write failed
    FILE_FLUSHING --> ERROR_BROADCAST: fsync failed
    ERROR_BROADCAST --> RELEASED: wake all waiters with exception

    RELEASED --> IDLE
    FLUSHED --> RELEASED
    IDLE --> [*]

    note right of WAITING_WRITTEN
        Waiter holds only wait slot.
        It must not hold redo file lock, Buffer Pool list lock, or page latch.
    end note

    note right of FILE_WRITING
        Writer does not call back into MTR, Buffer Pool, or LockManager.
    end note

